xplicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13280:\"<p>Want to use Blog Designer WordPress plugin in your Magento store?</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry..we have the solution..!!</p>\n<p>To start blogging with Magento website is never easy. There are so many blog extensions for Magento and you have to choose the best among them.</p>\n<p>But the main question is whose reference you should take to create your Magento blog with WordPress plugin. It&#8217;s very difficult to change the default blog page design in Magento.</p>\n<p><strong>The best part?</strong></p>\n<p>Today I am going to show you how to connect your Magento store with WordPress Blog Designer plugin. I&#8217;ll reveal the whole process in 4 easy steps. And it&#8217;ll take just 10 minutes to interpret. Isn&#8217;t it awesome..?</p>\n<p>I have experienced some difficulties to setup all things as per described below but once it&#8217;s done successfully then I understood the power of blogging with my existing Magento website. </p>\n<p>So, I thought I should share this to the people who are looking for blog with Magento site.</p>\n<h3>Why every Magento site must have a blog?</h3>\n<p>Blogs play a huge role in publishing valuable information about news and offers, upcoming product news, customer feedbacks, etc.</p>\n<p>It has great benefits from SEO point of view because through blog you can do promotion and marketing on social media which in return draws good traffic on website and eventually benefits of ranking higher in search listings.</p>\n<p>WordPress blog provides you basic features like categories, tags, comments, featured images, etc., where blog readers can play with your blog section. It is also gives you facility to change your theme design, improving blog functionality by adding some plugins, header and footer changes which suits to your existing Magento store.</p>\n<p>Now I am going to demonstrate the migration process from Magento to WordPress.</p>\n<p><strong>But before that, consider this:</strong></p>\n<p>You must have Magento 1.6.x, 1.7.x, 1.8.x or 1.9.x setup with community Edition. (We haven’t try with Enterprise Edition, you can try it with own risk)</p>\n<p>And I will write down same blog for Magento 2.x later once all R&amp;D completed from our side.</p>\n<p><strong>Now, let’s move on to the final steps. I have finalized steps and that are listed below.</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Install WordPress integration Magento extension</li>\n<li>Setup WordPress configuration and select blog path</li>\n<li>Write down 2-3 dummy blog posts to check on front-end</li>\n<li>Install Blog Designer Lite/PRO plugin to add beautiful designs to blog</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Starting from the first,</p>\n<h2>1. Install &#8216;WordPress Integration&#8217; Magento Extension</h2>\n<p>First of all, say many thanks to Magento Commerce community that providing a WordPress integration extension. You can download that extension with <a href=\"https://www.magentocommerce.com/magento-connect/wordpress-integration-1.html\" target=\"_blank\"> this link</a> as no cost, it&#8217;s free! </p>\n<p>If you are not a regular user of this website then sign up first then logged in with site to download your free copy.</p>\n<p>You need to press on &#8220;Install Now&#8221; button to select your <a href=\"https://www.magentocommerce.com/magento-connect/\" target=\"_blank\">Magento Connect version</a>. We have selected here Magento Connect 1.0 with dropdown selection. See below image for more details.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_20983\" style=\"width: 830px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension.png\" alt=\"WordPress Integration  Magento Extension\" width=\"820\" height=\"350\" class=\"size-full wp-image-20983\" srcset=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension.png 820w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension-300x128.png 300w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension-768x328.png 768w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension-500x213.png 500w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension-624x266.png 624w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-magento-extension-350x149.png 350w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Download &#8216;WordPress Integration&#8217; Magento Extension</p></div>\n<p><strong>Note:-</strong> If you are facing an any difficulty to download your free copy, then you can also download that same extension copy from <a href=\"http://freegento.com/magento-extensions/Fishpig_Wordpress_Integration-4.2.0.27.tgz\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<h2>2. Setup WordPress configuration and select blog path</h2>\n<p>Now, setup your downloaded extension file with your Magento setup. Below one is very basic steps to install Magento extension with your Magento setup. </p>\n<p>1) Download the .zip/.tgz file<br />\n2) Extract the contents of the .zip/.tgz file to your root folder<br />\n3) Log in to Admin Panel<br />\n4) Now, you can see a menu named &#8216;WordPress&#8217;<br />\n5) Clear Cache and Login again if you are not seeing that menu item</p>\n<p>Please go to <strong>WordPress &gt; Setup</strong> Menu to do further remaining steps to start blog section.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_21081\" style=\"width: 830px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel.png\" alt=\"WordPress Integration Settings Panel\" width=\"820\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-21081\" srcset=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel.png 820w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel-300x128.png 300w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel-768x328.png 768w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel-500x213.png 500w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel-624x266.png 624w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-settings-panel-350x149.png 350w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">WordPress Integration &#8211; Settings Panel</p></div>\n<p>Read each and every settings carefully and do that settings one by one. You can also get an idea from below image. That may be more useful to you with backend panel screenshot.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_21082\" style=\"width: 830px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration.png\" alt=\"WordPress Integration Configuration\" width=\"820\" height=\"469\" class=\"size-full wp-image-21082\" srcset=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration.png 820w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration-300x172.png 300w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration-768x439.png 768w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration-500x286.png 500w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration-624x357.png 624w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wordpress-integration-configuration-350x200.png 350w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">WordPress Integration &#8211; Configuration Steps</p></div>\n<p>Now, you are done with all <strong>WordPress Integration</strong> Extension settings. It&#8217;s time to start play with your new WordPress panel. If you have setup your blog path same like above image then you can access your WordPress frontend via <strong>http://your_magento_path/blog</strong> link.</p>\n<p>And if you want to start any update with backend settings then try to access this link &#8211; <strong>http://your_magento_path/blog/wp-admin</strong></p>\n<h2>3. Write down 2-3 dummy blog posts to check on frontend</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Writing_Posts\" target=\"_blank\">Writing Posts</a> is a good practice as you can write some blog posts with WordPress. Create posts, categories, tags. etc. If you haven&#8217;t write any blog before with any blogging tool then I would like to suggest please see below video.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/171021907\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" frameborder=\"0\" title=\"Creating Posts in WordPress\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><em><strong>Creating Posts in WordPress</strong></em></p>\n<p>I think, now you are done with all WordPress basic steps &#8211; how to publish new blog post, how to comment on existing blog posts, etc. More advanced, site owner can create number of users, give them role with capabilities and much more!</p>\n<h2>4. Install Blog Designer Lite/PRO plugin to add beautiful designs to blog</h2>\n<p>Choose the best blog design, it&#8217;s our main moto now! WordPress has lots of themes and plugins as a free and premium where you can select any one and can continue your newly created blog section.</p>\n<p>But think, if you would like to change design of blog section then it will be again more difficult question for us. We have already created a solution for all blog lovers..!!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/blog-designer/stats/\" target=\"_blank\">40K+ users</a> are already using our free solution with WordPress sites and there are 1500 users are using PRO version of Blog Designer.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_21087\" style=\"width: 830px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://codecanyon.net/item/blog-designer-pro-for-wordpress/17069678?ref=solwin\"><img src=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin.jpeg\" alt=\"Blog Designer PRO WordPress Plugin\" width=\"820\" height=\"352\" class=\"size-full wp-image-21087\" srcset=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin.jpeg 820w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin-300x129.jpeg 300w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin-768x330.jpeg 768w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin-500x215.jpeg 500w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin-624x268.jpeg 624w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blog-designer-pro-wordpress-plugin-350x150.jpeg 350w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Blog Designer PRO WordPress Plugin</p></div>\n<p>We are highly recommending to use <a href=\"http://blogdesigner.solwininfotech.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Blog Designer PRO</a> version for everyone because it will remove all your limits with new blog section. You no need to worry about if you are not more familiar with WordPress, CSS, jQuery and HTML or if you haven&#8217;t idea about how to customize current blog design.</p>\n<p>Blog Designer PRO is an all-in-one and powerful tool for any kind of WordPress blog websites. There are 26 unique and beautiful blog templates that will fulfill requirements of any blog page. It comes with amazing <a href=\"http://blogdesigner.solwininfotech.com/demo/blog-story-timeline-blog-template/\" target=\"_blank\">Timeline templates</a> and <a href=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/blog/wordpress/blog-designer-plugin-for-your-wordpress-website/\" target=\"_blank\">advanced benefits</a>.</p>\n<h3>Where Blog Designer WordPress plugin is useful in your Magento website?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li> To start new blog section</li>\n<li> Business &amp; Technology idea sharing</li>\n<li> Sharing your company story and achievement(timeline)</li>\n<li> Company new product updates</li>\n<li> Latest fashion ideas and offers</li>\n<li> Latest finance trends before purchase an item</li>\n<li> Online shopping tips &amp; tricks</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>That’s it. You&#8217;ve done it!!</strong></p>\n<p>I’m more than confident that your initial blog setup should now be finished and ready to go.<br />\nAll that should have been really damn easy (unlike my first time, lucky you!). </p>\n<p>If you are having any problems to start a new blog section with existing Magento website then this guide may help.</p>\n<p>If have any questions for me about how to create a blog, just get in touch with me or leave a comment below. I’ll help you out with any problems.</p>\n<p>Enjoy your new blog with Magento site!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/blog/start-blogging-magento-website-via-blog-designer-wordpress-plugin/\">How to Add WordPress Blog in Your Magento Store With Blog Designer Plugin? (Step-By-Step Guide)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com\">Solwin Infotech</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/blog/start-blogging-magento-website-via-blog-designer-wordpress-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base