 strong showcase list for our most successful product. Here is a free set of 100+ themes hacks for Blog Designer Pro plugin.</p>\n<p>We have received a lot of request in our support portal from Blog Designer PRO users. So, our support team has decided to write one global post for everyone. This way, we can guide to our customers in correct direction instead of waiting for support.</p>\n<p>Let’s move on to the question why this hack is required..? Every premium and free WordPress theme providers are publishing theme on regular basis and with own frameworks. So, sometimes its not possible to fit with the theme structure and to make it compatible with Blog Designer PRO plugin.</p>\n<p>For example, the theme provides a sidebar within main post content area instead of total different section with content area and then if you will apply single post settings with Blog Designer PRO plugin then it may mess up your current single post design.</p>\n<p>So we&#8217;ve decided to resolve this issue permanently. We are inspired by a WooCommerce and implemented a template override feature with the Blog Designer PRO plugin. Just duplicate your correct theme file, put it under required &#8220;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">bdp_templates</span>&#8221; folder, modify it according documentation <a href=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/documents/wordpress/blogdesigner/#archivepost_overwrite\" target=\"_blank\">steps</a> and enjoy your newly designed category/tag/author pages. Same thing for single post/article page also.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_20325\" style=\"width: 830px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Blog-Designer-Override-Folder-Structure.jpg\" alt=\"Blog Designer WordPress Plugin\" width=\"820\" height=\"350\" class=\"size-full wp-image-20325\" srcset=\"https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Blog-Designer-Override-Folder-Structure.jpg 820w, https://www.solwininfotech.com/wp-conten