(497, 257, 'panels_data', 'a:3:{s:7:\"widgets\";a:3:{i:0;a:6:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:1299:\"<p>I\'m a Minnesota-born &amp; raised girl with a Notre Dame education (math &amp; <a href=\"http://kroc.nd.edu/about-us/what-peace-studies\" target=\"_blank\">international peace studies</a>) living in Portland, Oregon.</p><p>After two years of teaching math at a <a href=\"http://www.waldencommunityschool.com/\" target=\"_blank\">community-based secondary school</a>, I learned that although I loved teaching, it exhausted my introverted self.</p><p>After moving around the country for a few years working jobs in food justice and alternative education, I decided to branch out on my own by starting Katie Tutors Math.</p><p>I\'ve fallen in love with helping students across the country and the world from the convenience of their own homes. I love working with my students one-on-one to help them understand math a little bit better each day and to watch their confidence in themselves grow. I\'m blessed to do what I love.</p><h5>And here are some details, in bullet points, so you know I\'m legit:</h5><ul><li>B.S. in Mathematics &amp; International Peace Studies, University of Notre Dame</li><li>10 years of experience tutoring over 200 students</li><li>ACT: 35 (Math: 36, Science: 36, English: 35, Reading: 33) 99th percentile</li><li>GRE Quantitative: 170 (GRE Verbal: 164) 99th percentile</li></ul>\";s:20:\"text_selected_editor\";s:4:\"tmce\";s:5:\"autop\";b:1;s:12:\"_sow_form_id\";s:13:\"57e058e0864a9\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:6:{s:5:\"class\";s:31:\"SiteOrigin_Widget_Editor_Widget\";s:4:\"grid\";i:0;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:0;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"da1f242c-6bb9-4344-be1f-658ebbea2f1c\";s:5:\"style\";a:4:{s:27:\"background_image_attachment\";b:0;s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";s:17:\"iw-visible-screen\";s:6:\"iw-all\";s:17:\"iw-visible-layout\";s:6:\"iw-all\";}}}i:1;a:6:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:200:\"<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-200\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_2236-e1474320425233.jpg\" alt=\"Katie the Math Tutor\" width=\"2064\" height=\"536\" /></p>\";s:20:\"text_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";s:5:\"autop\";b:1;s:12:\"_sow_form_id\";s:13:\"57e058b3705e7\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:7:{s:5:\"class\";s:31:\"SiteOrigin_Widget_Editor_Widget\";s:3:\"raw\";b:0;s:4:\"grid\";i:1;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:1;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"7871ec73-902e-4d55-836c-244f169fb0ff\";s:5:\"style\";a:1:{s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";}}}i:2;a:6:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:822:\"<h5>And just for fun:</h5><p>- I love local food. I spent a year in Spokane through <a href=\"https://jvcnorthwest.org/\" target=\"_blank\">JVC Northwest</a> working on <a href=\"http://www.catholiccharitiesfoodforall.org/\" target=\"_blank\">food access</a>. I now work at my <a href=\"http://www.montavillamarket.org/\" target=\"_blank\">neighborhood farmers market</a> in Portland crunching numbers and supporting our awesome community of volunteers.</p><p>- I love nature and plan on hiking 460 miles of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Crest_Trail\" target=\"_blank\">PCT</a> in 2018.</p><p>- I\'ve had four concussions, three in 2016, and am passionate about education around care of concussions and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Post-concussion_syndrome\" target=\"_blank\">post-concussion syndrome</a>.</p>\";s:20:\"text_selected_editor\";s:4:\"tmce\";s:5:\"autop\";b:1;s:12:\"_sow_form_id\";s:13:\"57e058f6c5f1b\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:6:{s:5:\"class\";s:31:\"SiteOrigin_Widget_Editor_Widget\";s:4:\"grid\";i:2;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:2;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"e625831d-55ab-490f-b252-8d468e52846a\";s:5:\"style\";a:4:{s:27:\"background_image_attachment\";b:0;s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";s:17:\"iw-visible-screen\";s:6:\"iw-all\";s:17:\"iw-visible-layout\";s:6:\"iw-all\";}}}}s:5:\"grids\";a:3:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"cells\";i:1;s:5:\"style