(26, 1, '2016-08-05 01:03:02', '2016-08-05 01:03:02', '<div><u>My story:</u></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>I\'m a Minnesota-born girl with a Notre Dame education (math &amp; international peace studies) living in the lush greenness of Portland, Oregon.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After a semester teaching math at a community-based secondary school, I was promoted to lead teacher handling administrative duties of a growing school and teaching all upper-level math courses. (I also wore many hats such as driving a van-full of squirrely middle-schoolers to tennis each week.)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>I learned that although I loved teaching math, it exhausted my introverted self, whatwith being on stage in front of teenagers all day. I took a leap and moved to Spokane, Washington to work in food access for a year.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Soon after I moved to Portland. During my first year, I tutored math at a a residential alcohol &amp; drug treatment center, a youth homeless center, and in an after-school program for newly arrived immigrant and refugee students.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>I loved these jobs. But due to a concussion and post-concussive syndrome, I quit in spring 2016.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>A blessing in disguise, my scanner nature began to flourish and I took the opportunity to focus on entrepreneurship.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>My current passion project is a platform that uses research-backed strategies to help people learn math -- specifically those preparing for the GED.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>I tutor math because it\'s fun, I\'m very good at it, and it funds my passion project. (And I get to help people like you, and I think that\'s pretty great.)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><u>Want to know more?</u></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- I love local food. I spent a year in Spokane, Washington as an AmeriCorps member through JVC Northwest working on food access. I now work at my neighborhood farmers market in Portland crunching numbers and supporting our awesome community of volunteers.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- I dream of permaculture and homesteading, propagate succulents on the reg, and plan on hiking 460 miles of the PCT in 2017.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- My first job at 15 was teaching piano lessons out of my family\'s living room.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- I\'ve had four concussions, three in 2016, and am passionate about education around care of concussions and post-concussive syndrome.</div>', 'About Me', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-05 01:03:02', '2016-08-05 01:03:02', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/2016/08/05/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
