(55, 1, '2016-08-09 16:02:37', '2016-08-09 23:02:37', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I\'m a Minnesota-born girl with a Notre Dame education (math &amp; international peace studies) living in Portland, Oregon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">After a semester teaching math at a community-based secondary school, I was promoted to lead teacher handling administrative duties of a growing school and teaching all upper-level math courses.<em> (I also wore many hats such as driving a van-full of squirrely middle-schoolers to tennis each week.)</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I learned that although<strong> I loved teaching math,</strong> it exhausted my introverted self, whatwith being on stage in front of teenagers all day.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I took a leap and moved to Spokane, Washington to work in food access for a year.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Soon after I moved to Portland. I tutored math at a a residential alcohol &amp; drug treatment center, a youth homeless center, and in an after-school program for newly arrived immigrant and refugee students.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>I loved these jobs.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">But due to a concussion and post-concussive syndrome, I quit in spring 2016.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A blessing in disguise, my scanner nature began to flourish and I took the opportunity to focus on entrepreneurship.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">My current passion project is a platform that uses research-backed strategies to help people learn math -- specifically those preparing for the GED.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I tutor math because it\'s fun, I\'m <em>very</em> good at it, and it helps fund my passion project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">(And I get to help people like you, and I think that\'s pretty great.)</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Want to know more?</h3>\r\nI love local food. I spent a year in Spokane, Washington as an AmeriCorps member through JVC Northwest working on food access. I now work at my neighborhood farmers market in Portland crunching numbers and supporting our awesome community of volunteers.\r\n\r\nI dream of permaculture and homesteading, propagate succulents on the reg, and plan on hiking 460 miles of the PCT in 2017.\r\n\r\nMy first job at 15 was teaching piano lessons out of my family\'s living room.\r\n\r\nI\'ve had four concussions, three in 2016, and am passionate about education around care of concussions and post-concussive syndrome.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-09 16:02:37', '2016-08-09 23:02:37', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(56, 1, '2016-08-09 16:03:03', '2016-08-09 23:03:03', 'Tutoring is a privilege.\r\n\r\nIn my work, I witness a student\'s willingness to be vulnerable and make mistakes.\r\n\r\nI walk alongside them in that vulnerable place where learning and growth happen.\r\n\r\nI don\'t take this lightly.\r\n\r\nFrankly, it\'s a <em>sacred</em> space.\r\n\r\nAnd sure, the acquisition of knowledge is great, but what I relish in is the increase in self-confidence and self-efficacy, and the growth in a willingness to try.\r\n\r\nAnd I love math.\r\n\r\nYou see, the thing is, <strong>I think math is fun.</strong>\r\n\r\nIt\'s like a game or puzzle that I get to play with. There is one right answer, so I know when I\'m on track, but there are always many many ways to arrive at that answer, many ways to think about it and make it make sense in my brain. It\'s so fun.\r\n\r\nAnd <strong>I love sharing this</strong> with other people.\r\n\r\nBecause I think after I do, you might think math is fun too.\r\n\r\n<em>Or, at least, you won\'t think it\'s so hard.</em>\r\n\r\nBecause math doesn\'t have to be hard.\r\n\r\nHas it felt hard?\r\n\r\nLet\'s get you a guide.\r\n\r\nA tutor.\r\n\r\nSomeone who knows when to nudge, when to sit in silence and wait to let your brain make the connection, when to support, affirm, or encourage.\r\n\r\n<em>Ahem,</em> that\'s me.\r\n\r\nI\'m a great listener, highly empathetic, and have a great intuitive sense combined with thousands of hours of experience to know how you learn best in each moment.\r\n\r\nIf this sounds like something you are jiving with, let\'s work together.', 'Philosophy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-09 16:03:03', '2016-08-09 23:03:03', '', 17, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/17-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
