(116, 1, '2016-08-09 22:57:03', '2016-08-10 05:57:03', '<img class=\"wp-image-18  alignright\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/P1050913.jpg\" alt=\"Katie Math Tutor\" width=\"155\" height=\"205\" />\r\n\r\nI\'m a Minnesota-born girl with a Notre Dame education (math &amp; international peace studies) living in Portland, Oregon.\r\n\r\nAfter two years of teaching math at a community-based secondary school, I learned that although I loved teaching, it exhausted my introverted self (whatwith being on stage in front of teenagers all day).\r\n\r\nSoon after I moved to Portland. During my first year, I tutored math at a a residential alcohol &amp; drug treatment center, a youth homeless center, and in an after-school program for newly arrived immigrant and refugee students.\r\n\r\nI loved these jobs. But due to a concussion and post-concussive syndrome, I quit in spring 2016.\r\n\r\nA blessing in disguise, my scanner nature began to flourish and I took the opportunity to focus on entrepreneurship.\r\n\r\n<em>My current passion project is a platform that uses research-backed strategies to help people learn math -- specifically those preparing for the GED.</em>\r\n\r\nBut back to math tutoring... I tutor math because it\'s fun, I\'m very good at it, and it funds my passion project. (And I get to help people like you, and I think that\'s pretty great.)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>And here are some details, in bullet points, so you know I\'m legit:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>B.S. in Mathematics &amp; International Peace Studies, University of Notre Dame</li>\r\n 	<li>ACT: 35 (Math: 36, Science: 36, English: 35, Reading: 33) 99th percentile</li>\r\n 	<li>GRE Quantitative: 170 (GRE Verbal: 164) 99th percentile</li>\r\n 	<li>10 years of experience tutoring over 200 students</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>And just for fun:</h5>\r\n- I love local food. I spent a year in Spokane, Washington as an AmeriCorps member through <a href=\"https://jvcnorthwest.org/\" target=\"_blank\">JVC Northwest</a> working on <a href=\"http://www.catholiccharitiesfoodforall.org/\" target=\"_blank\">food access</a>. I now work at my <a href=\"http://www.montavillamarket.org/\" target=\"_blank\">neighborhood farmers market</a> in Portland crunching numbers and supporting our awesome community of volunteers.\r\n\r\n- I dream of permaculture and homesteading, propagate succulents on the reg, and plan on hiking 460 miles of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Crest_Trail\" target=\"_blank\">PCT</a> in 2017.\r\n\r\n- My first job at 15 was teaching piano lessons out of my family\'s living room.\r\n\r\n- I\'ve had four concussions, three in 2016, and am passionate about education around care of concussions and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Post-concussion_syndrome\" target=\"_blank\">post-concussion syndrome</a>.', 'About Me', 'Welcome to Katie Tutors Math', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-09 22:57:03', '2016-08-10 05:57:03', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
