(138, 1, '2017-02-02 08:44:44', '2017-02-02 16:44:44', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<h6>How often should my child have tutoring sessions?</h6>\nFrequency of sessions depends on the student\'s needs and goals. Most students schedule for one or two times weekly. (I generally find that students who schedule at least two times weekly make the most progress.) If a student is motivated and needs the help, tremendous progress can be made with sessions three times per week or more.\n\nSessions can also be scheduled on an as-needed basis, or if a regularly-scheduled student needs extra help one week (such as due to an upcoming test). An online scheduling system for these slots makes signing up simple and eliminates email/phone tag.\n<h6></h6>\n<h6></h6>\n<h6>When are you available for tutoring?</h6>\nAs of January 2017, I tutor Mondays - Thursdays 1 - 8 pm PST (that\'s 3-10 pm CST and 4 - 11 pm EST). I occasionally tutor on Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays by request.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6>How does online tutoring work?</h6>\nStudents must have access to a computer, high-speed internet, and a webcam. During the session, the student and I will use Skype or Google Hangouts to see and hear each other, and an <a href=\"http://scribblar.com/\">online whiteboard</a> that we both can write on using a mouse or <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Wacom-Bamboo-CTL471-Tablet-Black/dp/B00EVOXM3S/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1472429661&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=wacom+bamboo+tablet&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=a2c5b0a5d85dc1df044782d4c4402df9&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\" target=\"_blank\">tablet</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />. We can also upload any images or worksheets into the whiteboard. It\'s surprisingly easy!\n\nI do a 30-minute consultation with each new student so he or she feels comfortable with the technology before our first session.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6>Do you tutor in person?</h6>\nNope! I am no longer accepting new in-person students. Since I had my first online student, I\'ve come to see that online tutoring works just as well, if not better, than in person tutoring.\n\nIf you want to find an in-person tutor, I recommend <a href=\"https://www.wyzant.com/\">WyzAnt</a>, which is the most popular database of tutors. If you use this link (<a href=\"https://goo.gl/lC3sSp\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=https://goo.gl/lC3sSp&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1483496273221000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGd4QE1OdJKYiJGpMc44EEcLbzZCg\">https://goo.gl/lC3sSp</a>), you can sign up for a free account and get a $40 credit for your first session. (Ignore that my profile shows up, after you sign up you can search and find tutors in your area.)\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6>What are your rates?</h6>\nMy rates reflect my experience and the quality of service you will receive. Yes, there are many other cheaper tutors out there, but keep in mind that results tend to be directly correlated to how much you invest in an experience.\n\n60 minute session - $60\n\n30 minute session - $32\n\n<em>(Note that all sessions end a few minutes early to allow me a short break between sessions.)</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6></h6>\n<h6>Can you help me prepare for the SAT/ACT/GRE?</h6>\nI am no longer tutoring students to specifically prepare for standardized tests (except the GED). There are many excellent online tutors who specialize in these tests, and I am happy to give you a referral.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6>Can you help me in other subjects besides math?</h6>\nI primarily tutor math (as you surely have deduced by now!). That said, I also love tutoring beginning Spanish. (In college I spent summers in Guatemala and Ecuador on language immersion and took Spanish classes up to a 300-level.)\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6>How does payment work?</h6>\nFor sessions that are scheduled as needed: payment is required by card at the time of scheduling.\n\nFor regularly scheduled weekly sessions: Invoices are sent monthly via email and can be paid by card. Payment is due by the first session of each month.\n\nAny tutoring sessions missed in accordance with the cancellation policy will be refunded by pro-rating the following month, unless the student or parent requests otherwise.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h6>What is your cancellation policy?</h6>\nThis business is my main source of income. That said, my cancellation policy is my very best attempt to balance fairness to the student and to myself. Additionally, tutoring is a valuable commitment, and showing up to each tutoring session helps the student create momentum in their learning.\n\n- I ask that you let me know about a cancellation as soon as possible.\n\n- I require a 48 hour notice for a cancellation in order to not be charged. Sessions canceled with less than 48 hours notice must be paid in full.\n\n- Excessive cancellations may be reason for ending tutoring services.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-02 08:44:44', '2017-02-02 16:44:44', '', 132, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/132-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(139, 1, '2016-08-18 15:23:50', '2016-08-18 22:23:50', '<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\r\n<h6>What are your rates?</h6>\r\n$60/hour (for 1 hour or more). $35/half-hour session.\r\n<h6></h6>\r\n<h6>What is your cancellation policy?</h6>\r\nThis business is my main source of income. That said, my cancellation policy is my very best attempt to balance fairness to the student and to myself. Additionally, tutoring is a valuable commitment, and showing up to each tutoring session helps the student create momentum in their learning.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">- I ask that you let me know about a cancellation as soon as possible. </span>\r\n\r\n- I require a 48 hour notice for a cancellation in order to not be charged. Sessions canceled within 24 to 48 hours notice incur a 50% session-fee. Sessions canceled with less than 24 hours notice must be paid in full.\r\n\r\n- Sicknesses and emergencies sometimes occur. These will be handled on a case-by-case basis.\r\n\r\n- Excessive cancellations will be handled on a case-by-case basis and may be ground for discontinuing tutoring services.\r\n<h6>How does payment work?</h6>\r\nAfter a trial period, payment is due by the first session of each month by cash, check, or credit card. The trial period is generally 1-3 lessons and is agreed upon by myself and the client by the first tutoring session. During the trial period, payment is due at session time.\r\n\r\nNote that any tutoring sessions missed in accordance with the cancellation policy will be refunded by pro-rating the following month, unless the student or parent requests otherwise.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em>Additional FAQs coming soon</em>\r\n<h5></h5>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-18 15:23:50', '2016-08-18 22:23:50', '', 132, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
