(201, 1, '2016-09-19 14:28:46', '2016-09-19 21:28:46', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I\'m a Minnesota-born &amp; raised girl with a Notre Dame education (math &amp; <a href=\"http://kroc.nd.edu/about-us/what-peace-studies\" target=\"_blank\">international peace studies</a>) living in Portland, Oregon.</p>\r\n<p>After two years of teaching math at a <a href=\"http://www.waldencommunityschool.com/\" target=\"_blank\">community-based secondary school</a>, I learned that although I loved teaching, it exhausted my introverted self (whatwith being on stage in front of teenagers all day).</p>\r\n<p>Soon after I moved to Portland. I&nbsp;tutored math at an alcohol &amp; drug treatment center, a homeless center, and for newly arrived immigrant and refugee students.</p>\r\n<p>I loved these jobs. But due to a concussion and post-concussive syndrome, I quit in spring 2016.</p>\r\n<p>A blessing in disguise, my&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Refuse-Choose-Interests-Passions-Hobbies/dp/1594866260?&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=b805ff30ed4020a66e74e33b08d07de0&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\" target=\"_blank\">scanner</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\"> nature began to flourish and I took the opportunity to focus on entrepreneurship.</p>\r\n<p>(My current passion project is a platform that uses research-backed strategies to help people learn math -- specifically those preparing for the GED.)</p>\r\n<p>But back to math tutoring... I tutor math because it\'s fun, I\'m very good at it, and it funds my passion project. (And I get to help people like you, and I think that\'s pretty great.)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h5>And here are some details, in bullet points, so you know I\'m legit:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.S. in Mathematics &amp; International Peace Studies, University of Notre Dame</li>\r\n<li>10 years of experience tutoring over 200 students</li>\r\n<li>ACT: 35 (Math: 36, Science: 36, English: 35, Reading: 33) 99th percentile</li>\r\n<li>GRE Quantitative: 170 (GRE Verbal: 164) 99th percentile</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5></h5>\r\n<h5>And just for fun:</h5>\r\n<p>- I love local food. I spent a year in Spokane through <a href=\"https://jvcnorthwest.org/\" target=\"_blank\">JVC Northwest</a> working on <a href=\"http://www.catholiccharitiesfoodforall.org/\" target=\"_blank\">food access</a>. I now work at my <a href=\"http://www.montavillamarket.org/\" target=\"_blank\">neighborhood farmers market</a> in Portland crunching numbers and supporting our awesome community of volunteers.</p>\r\n<p>- I love nature and plan on hiking 460 miles of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Crest_Trail\" target=\"_blank\">PCT</a> in 2018.</p>\r\n<p>- I\'ve had four concussions, three in 2016, and am passionate about education around care of concussions and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Post-concussion_syndrome\" target=\"_blank\">post-concussion syndrome</a>.</p>', 'About Me', 'Welcome to Katie Tutors Math', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-19 14:28:46', '2016-09-19 21:28:46', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
