r as short as you wish, and if you find a great tutor, you can develop a relationship with him or her and request them for tutoring in the future. You can also see student reviews of each tutor, which is helpful. The platform includes an online whiteboard with text chat and optional audio and video.Although it is set up and usually used for short sessions, longer sessions do happen. I worked with one student on InstaEDU and helped her through her College Algebra class with sessions 1-3 times per week for the duration of the semester. Sometimes our sessions lasted over two hours!</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Limitations:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Quality of tutoring varies greatly amongst tutors (however there are many reviews, so it’s fairly easy to find a great tutor!)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"qlink_container\"><a class=\"external_link\" href=\"https://www.mathelf.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\"><b>MathElf</b></a></span> is up and coming. It instantly connects you to a random tutor, but you can also schedule sessions with tutors you have had in the past, making it the best of both worlds. You use a shared whiteboard and audio via your iPad, and they send you a free pen to use with your iPad! The tutors care greatly about the students and will work diligently to help you, often collaborating in Slack to do so. The commitment of these tutors and this organization is superb.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Limitations:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>It’s a small start-up, so at odd hours (say, the middle of the night for US time zones) there may not be any tutors available.</li>\r\n 	<li>You must use an iPad.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"qlink_container\"><a class=\"external_link\" href=\"https://www.yup.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\"><b>Yup</b></a></span> (formerly MathCrunch) is great for students who have a quick homework problem. Using your mobile phone, you are instantly connected with a random tutor. You upload a photo of your math problem and then have a chat box to share with the tutor.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Limitations:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>You have to use a mobile phone, and it can be difficult to get help with your math problem on such a small screen.</li>\r\n 	<li>Many of the tutors are from different countries where English is not the first language, which can make communication difficult.</li>\r\n 	<li>There is no audio or whiteboard available -- the only communication comes from the chat box.</li>\r\n 	<li>Quality of tutoring varies greatly amongst tutors.</li>\r\n 	<li>Students have no option to choose a tutor — it’s completely random each time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-244 alignright\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/happy-online-math-student-tutor.jpg\" alt=\"happy-online-math-student-tutor\" width=\"450\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nIt takes about five minutes to get set up with any of these online tutoring platforms. Choose the one that sounds best to you, and get going. That math homework isn\'t going to do itself!\r\n\r\nIf you are looking for a more personal relationship with your math tutor, I recommend finding a private math tutor. You can use a search engine to find a tutor or use a site such as <a href=\"https://www.wyzant.com/\">WyzAnt</a>, <a href=\"http://www.universitytutor.com/\">UniversityTutor</a>, or <a href=\"http://www.nextguru.com/\">NextGuru</a> where tutors have profiles listed and, often, reviews. Find one that you are comfortable with and ask for a free trial session to begin with to make sure it will be a great fit for you.\r\n\r\n<em>Interested in hiring me as your online math tutor? I offer a free 30-minute trial session to all new students. Learn more <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/tutoring/\">here</a>.</em>', 'Online Math Tutoring: The Top 3 Sites', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '182-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-30 13:57:52', '2016-09-30 20:57:52', '', 182, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/182-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
