nute consultation today\r\n\r\n<a class=\"call-to-action-button\" title=\"Schedule\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/free-consultation/\">Schedule</a>\r\n\r\nI’ve been coming to Katie for tutoring for quite some time, and she’s finally seeing me out the door. I truly have her to thank for my success in my math courses. She has me walking away with confidence and understanding that just wasn’t there prior to our sessions. She’s always patient, kind and helpful. She makes learning the way it should be – FUN. Thanks again, Katie.\r\n\r\nAnna College Algebra, Online\r\n\r\nSimply the best! Katie is a very knowledgeable and extremely patient tutor. She is a huge part of me understanding and getting through Calc 1. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!\r\n\r\nRussell College Calculus, Returning Adult Student', 'Tutoring', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '72-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-02 17:15:34', '2016-12-03 01:15:34', '', 72, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/72-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(256, 1, '2016-12-02 17:20:25', '2016-12-03 01:20:25', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n<h6>What are your rates?</h6>\r\n55-minute sessions: $60.\r\n\r\n27-minute sessions: $32\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How often should my child have tutoring sessions?</h6>\r\nFrequency of sessions depends on the student\'s needs and goals. Most students schedule for one or two times weekly. (I generally find that students who schedule at least two times weekly make the most progress.) If a student is motivated and needs the help, tremendous progress can be made with sessions three times per week or more.\r\n\r\nSessions can also be scheduled on an as-needed basis, or if a regularly-scheduled student needs extra help one week (such as due to an upcoming test). An online scheduling system for these slots makes signing up simple and eliminates email/phone tag.\r\n<h6></h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How does online tutoring work?</h6>\r\nStudents must have access to a computer, high-speed internet, and a webcam. During the session, the student and I will use Skype or Google Hangouts to see and hear each other, and an <a href=\"http://scribblar.com/\">online whiteboard</a> that we both can write on using a mouse or <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Wacom-Bamboo-CTL471-Tablet-Black/dp/B00EVOXM3S/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1472429661&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=wacom+bamboo+tablet&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=a2c5b0a5d85dc1df044782d4c4402df9&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\" target=\"_blank\">tablet</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />. We can also upload any images or worksheets into the whiteboard. It\'s surprisingly easy!\r\n\r\nI do a 30-minute trial run with each new student so he or she feels comfortable with the technology before our first session.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>Do you tutor in person?</h6>\r\nI am no longer accepting new in-person students.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>What is your cancellation policy?</h6>\r\nThis business is my main source of income. That said, my cancellation policy is my very best attempt to balance fairness to the student and to myself. Additionally, tutoring is a valuable commitment, and showing up to each tutoring session helps the student create momentum in their learning.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">- I ask that you let me know about a cancellation as soon as possible. </span>\r\n\r\n- I require a 48 hour notice for a cancellation in order to not be charged. Sessions canceled with less than 48 hours notice must be paid in full.\r\n\r\n- Excessive cancellations may be reason for ending tutoring services.\r\n<h6></h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How does payment work?</h6>\r\nInvoices are sent via email and can be paid with a card. After a trial period, payment is due by the first session of each month. The trial period is generally 1-3 lessons and is agreed upon by myself and the client by the first tutoring session. During the trial period, payment is due at session time.\r\n\r\nAny tutoring sessions missed in accordance with the cancellation policy will be refunded by pro-rating the following month, unless the student or parent requests otherwise.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-02 17:20:25', '2016-12-03 01:20:25', '', 132, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(257, 1, '2016-12-02 17:30:23', '2016-12-03 01:30:23', 'I\'m a Minnesota-born &amp; raised girl with a Notre Dame education (math &amp; <a href=\"http://kroc.nd.edu/about-us/what-peace-studies\" target=\"_blank\">international peace studies</a>) living in Portland, Oregon.\r\n\r\nAfter two years of teaching math at a <a href=\"http://www.waldencommunityschool.com/\" target=\"_blank\">community-based secondary school</a>, I learned that although I loved teaching, it exhausted my introverted self (whatwith being on stage in front of teenagers all day).\r\n\r\nSoon after I moved to Portland. I tutored math at an alcohol &amp; drug treatment center, a homeless center, and for newly arrived immigrant and refugee students.\r\n\r\nI loved these jobs. But due to a concussion and post-concussive syndrome, I quit in spring 2016.\r\n\r\nA blessing in disguise, my <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Refuse-Choose-Interests-Passions-Hobbies/dp/1594866260?&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=b805ff30ed4020a66e74e33b08d07de0&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\" target=\"_blank\">scanner</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" /> nature began to flourish and I took the opportunity to focus on entrepreneurship.\r\n\r\n(My current passion project is a platform that uses research-backed strategies to help people learn math -- specifically those preparing for the GED.)\r\n\r\nBut back to math tutoring... I tutor math because it\'s fun, I\'m very good at it, and it funds my passion project. (And I get to help people like you, and I think that\'s pretty great.)\r\n<h5>And here are some details, in bullet points, so you know I\'m legit:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>B.S. in Mathematics &amp; International Peace Studies, University of Notre Dame</li>\r\n 	<li>10 years of experience tutoring over 200 students</li>\r\n 	<li>ACT: 35 (Math: 36, Science: 36, English: 35, Reading: 33) 99th percentile</li>\r\n 	<li>GRE Quantitative: 170 (GRE Verbal: 164) 99th percentile</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-200\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_2236-e1474320425233.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2064px) 100vw, 2064px\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_2236-e1474320425233.jpg 2064w, http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_2236-e1474320425233-300x78.jpg 300w, http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_2236-e1474320425233-768x199.jpg 768w, http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_2236-e1474320425233-1024x266.jpg 1024w\" alt=\"Katie the Math Tutor\" width=\"2064\" height=\"536\" />\r\n<h5>And just for fun:</h5>\r\n- I love local food. I spent a year in Spokane through <a href=\"https://jvcnorthwest.org/\" target=\"_blank\">JVC Northwest</a> working on <a href=\"http://www.catholiccharitiesfoodforall.org/\" target=\"_blank\">food access</a>. I now work at my <a href=\"http://www.montavillamarket.org/\" target=\"_blank\">neighborhood farmers market</a> in Portland crunching numbers and supporting our awesome community of volunteers.\r\n\r\n- I love nature and plan on hiking 460 miles of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Crest_Trail\" target=\"_blank\">PCT</a> in 2018.\r\n\r\n- I\'ve had four concussions, three in 2016, and am passionate about education around care of concussions and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Post-concussion_syndrome\" target=\"_blank\">post-concussion syndrome</a>.', 'About Me', 'Welcome to Katie Tutors Math', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-02 17:30:23', '2016-12-03 01:30:23', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
