(307, 1, '2016-12-30 14:08:52', '2016-12-30 22:08:52', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n<h6>How often should my child have tutoring sessions?</h6>\r\nFrequency of sessions depends on the student\'s needs and goals. Most students schedule for one or two times weekly. (I generally find that students who schedule at least two times weekly make the most progress.) If a student is motivated and needs the help, tremendous progress can be made with sessions three times per week or more.\r\n\r\nSessions can also be scheduled on an as-needed basis, or if a regularly-scheduled student needs extra help one week (such as due to an upcoming test). An online scheduling system for these slots makes signing up simple and eliminates email/phone tag.\r\n<h6></h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>What are your rates?</h6>\r\n50-minute sessions: $60.\r\n\r\n25-minute sessions: $32\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>When are you available for tutoring?</h6>\r\nAs of January 2017, I tutor Mondays - Thursdays 2 - 8 pm PST (that\'s 5 - 11 pm EST). If there is student interest in other times, I will consider expanding as my schedule allows.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How does online tutoring work?</h6>\r\nStudents must have access to a computer, high-speed internet, and a webcam. During the session, the student and I will use Skype or Google Hangouts to see and hear each other, and an <a href=\"http://scribblar.com/\">online whiteboard</a> that we both can write on using a mouse or <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Wacom-Bamboo-CTL471-Tablet-Black/dp/B00EVOXM3S/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1472429661&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=wacom+bamboo+tablet&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=a2c5b0a5d85dc1df044782d4c4402df9&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\" target=\"_blank\">tablet</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />. We can also upload any images or worksheets into the whiteboard. It\'s surprisingly easy!\r\n\r\nI do a 30-minute consultation with each new student so he or she feels comfortable with the technology before our first session.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>Do you tutor in person?</h6>\r\nNope! I am no longer accepting new in-person students. Since I had my first online student, I\'ve come to see that online tutoring works just as well, if not better, than in person tutoring.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>Can you help me prepare for the SAT/ACT/GRE?</h6>\r\nI am no longer tutoring students to specifically prepare for standardized tests. There are many excellent online tutors who specialize in these tests, and I am happy to give you a referral.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6></h6>\r\n<h6>Can you help me in other subjects besides math?</h6>\r\nI primarily tutor math (as you surely have deduced by now!). That said, I also tutor beginning Spanish. (I spent summers in Guatemala and Ecuador on language immersion in college and took Spanish classes up to a 300-level.)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How does payment work?</h6>\r\nFor regularly scheduled weekly sessions: Invoices are sent via email and can be paid with a card. After a trial period, payment is due by the first session of each month. The trial period is generally 1-3 lessons and is agreed upon by myself and the client by the first tutoring session. During the trial period, payment is due at session time.\r\n\r\nFor sessions that are scheduled as needed, payment is required by card at the time of scheduling.\r\n\r\nAny tutoring sessions missed in accordance with the cancellation policy will be refunded by pro-rating the following month, unless the student or parent requests otherwise.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>What is your cancellation policy?</h6>\r\nThis business is my main source of income. That said, my cancellation policy is my very best attempt to balance fairness to the student and to myself. Additionally, tutoring is a valuable commitment, and showing up to each tutoring session helps the student create momentum in their learning.\r\n\r\n- I ask that you let me know about a cancellation as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n- I require a 48 hour notice for a cancellation in order to not be charged. Sessions canceled with less than 48 hours notice must be paid in full.\r\n\r\n- Excessive cancellations may be reason for ending tutoring services.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-30 14:08:52', '2016-12-30 22:08:52', '', 132, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(308, 1, '2017-01-01 15:41:35', '2017-01-01 23:41:35', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n<h6>How often should my child have tutoring sessions?</h6>\r\nFrequency of sessions depends on the student\'s needs and goals. Most students schedule for one or two times weekly. (I generally find that students who schedule at least two times weekly make the most progress.) If a student is motivated and needs the help, tremendous progress can be made with sessions three times per week or more.\r\n\r\nSessions can also be scheduled on an as-needed basis, or if a regularly-scheduled student needs extra help one week (such as due to an upcoming test). An online scheduling system for these slots makes signing up simple and eliminates email/phone tag.\r\n<h6></h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>What are your rates?</h6>\r\n50-minute sessions: $60.\r\n\r\n25-minute sessions: $32\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>When are you available for tutoring?</h6>\r\nAs of January 2017, I tutor Mondays - Thursdays 2 - 8 pm PST (that\'s 5 - 11 pm EST). If there is student interest in other times, I will expand to other times and days as my schedule allows.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How does online tutoring work?</h6>\r\nStudents must have access to a computer, high-speed internet, and a webcam. During the session, the student and I will use Skype or Google Hangouts to see and hear each other, and an <a href=\"http://scribblar.com/\">online whiteboard</a> that we both can write on using a mouse or <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Wacom-Bamboo-CTL471-Tablet-Black/dp/B00EVOXM3S/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1472429661&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=wacom+bamboo+tablet&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=a2c5b0a5d85dc1df044782d4c4402df9&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\" target=\"_blank\">tablet</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />. We can also upload any images or worksheets into the whiteboard. It\'s surprisingly easy!\r\n\r\nI do a 30-minute consultation with each new student so he or she feels comfortable with the technology before our first session.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>Do you tutor in person?</h6>\r\nNope! I am no longer accepting new in-person students. Since I had my first online student, I\'ve come to see that online tutoring works just as well, if not better, than in person tutoring.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>Can you help me prepare for the SAT/ACT/GRE?</h6>\r\nI am no longer tutoring students to specifically prepare for standardized tests. There are many excellent online tutors who specialize in these tests, and I am happy to give you a referral.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>Can you help me in other subjects besides math?</h6>\r\nI primarily tutor math (as you surely have deduced by now!). That said, I also love tutoring beginning Spanish. (In college I spent summers in Guatemala and Ecuador on language immersion and took Spanish classes up to a 300-level.)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>How does payment work?</h6>\r\nFor regularly scheduled weekly sessions: Invoices are sent via email and can be paid with a card. After a trial period, payment is due by the first session of each month. The trial period is generally 1-3 lessons and is agreed upon by myself and the client by the first tutoring session. During the trial period, payment is due at session time.\r\n\r\nFor sessions that are scheduled as needed, payment is required by card at the time of scheduling.\r\n\r\nAny tutoring sessions missed in accordance with the cancellation policy will be refunded by pro-rating the following month, unless the student or parent requests otherwise.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h6>What is your cancellation policy?</h6>\r\nThis business is my main source of income. That said, my cancellation policy is my very best attempt to balance fairness to the student and to myself. Additionally, tutoring is a valuable commitment, and showing up to each tutoring session helps the student create momentum in their learning.\r\n\r\n- I ask that you let me know about a cancellation as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n- I require a 48 hour notice for a cancellation in order to not be charged. Sessions canceled with less than 48 hours notice must be paid in full.\r\n\r\n- Excessive cancellations may be reason for ending tutoring services.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-01 15:41:35', '2017-01-01 23:41:35', '', 132, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(309, 1, '2017-01-01 15:46:11', '2017-01-01 23:46:11', '<h4>News:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>If you ever need an extra tutoring session one week, you are welcome to <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/schedule-a-session/\">schedule a session</a> at your convenience! (Payment is due at time of scheduling, so have your card on hand.)</li>\r\n 	<li>You can always text or email me pictures of your assignments or anything that you\'d like to work on. No need to wait until our session time -- send them over a day or two early if you want.</li>\r\n 	<li>I use a <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00EVOXM3S/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B00EVOXM3S&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=katietutorsma-20&amp;linkId=dcd573e27dfe8561c669b4a6bf1d26a1\" target=\"_blank\">Wacom Bamboo Tablet</a><img style=\"border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;\" src=\"//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=katietutorsma-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B00EVOXM3S\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" /> to write on the whiteboard during tutoring sessions. It\'s definitely not required for students to have one, but check out the link if you are interested. Instead of using your computer mouse, you use a special pen to write on the tablet.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>Policies:</h2>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4>Late Policy</h4>\r\nGiving the student the opportunity to learn in a tutoring session is very important to me. The student should be on time to each tutoring session to allow us as much time as possible for them to get the help they need. In the event that the student is running late, the lost time will not be made up.\r\n<h4>Cancellations</h4>\r\nThis business is my main source of income. That said, my cancellation policy is my very best attempt to balance fairness to the student and to myself. Additionally, tutoring is a valuable commitment, and showing up to each tutoring session will help the student create momentum in their learning.\r\n\r\n- I ask that you let me know about a cancellation as soon as possible. Cancellations may be made by phone (text, call, or voicemail at 503-563-0713) or email (katietutorsmath@gmail.com).\r\n\r\n- I require a 48 hour notice for a cancellation in order to not be charged. Sessions canceled with less than 48 hours notice must be paid in full.\r\n\r\n- Excessive cancellations may be reason for ending tutoring services.\r\n<h4>Payment</h4>\r\nAfter a trial period, payment is due by the first session of each month by card. Your invoice will be emailed to you by the 1st of the month. If payment is not made at the first session of the month, then the student will not be able to receive tutoring until the payment is made. Note that any tutoring sessions missed in accordance with the cancellation policy will be refunded by pro-rating the following month, unless you request otherwise.\r\n\r\nDuring the trial period, each session must be paid by the time of the session by card via an invoice you will receive by email. The trial period will be for the first three sessions unless we have agreed to something different.\r\n\r\nIf you decide to stop tutoring at any time, all remaining sessions (at least 48 hours in the future) for the month will be refunded to you in accordance with the cancellation policy.', 'Current Students', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-01 15:46:11', '2017-01-01 23:46:11', '', 210, 'http://localhost:8888/ktm_wp/210-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
